not made a mistake. You are in the correct place to carry out the multiple =
regression procedure. This is just the title that SPSS Statistics gives, ev=
en when running a multiple regression procedure.</p>
	</li>
=09
	<li>You will be presented with the <strong>Linear Regression</strong> dial=
ogue box below:
	<div class=3D"spss-image" style=3D"max-width:535px;max-height: 470px;"><im=
g src=3D"https://statistics.laerd.com/spss-tutorials/img/mr/lr-20-dialogue-=
box.png" data-src=3D"img/mr/lr-20-dialogue-box.png" alt=3D"'Linear Regressi=
on' dialogue box for a multiple regression analysis in SPSS Statistics. All=
 variables on the left" width=3D"100%"><p>Published with written permission=
 from SPSS Statistics, IBM Corporation.</p>
			</div>
	</li>
=09
	<li>Transfer the dependent variable, <span class=3D"s-variable">VO<sub>2</=
sub>max</span>, into the <span class=3D"boxes"><u>D</u>ependent:</span> box=
 and the independent variables, <span class=3D"s-variable">age</span>, <spa=
n class=3D"s-variable">weight</span>, <span class=3D"s-variable">heart_rate=
</span> and <span class=3D"n-variable">gender</span> into the <span class=
=3D"boxes"><u>I</u>ndependent(s):</span> box, using the <img class=3D"spss-=
image-in-text" src=3D"https://statistics.laerd.com/spss-tutorials/img/mr/ar=
row-right-button.png" data-src=3D"img/mr/arrow-right-button.png" alt=3D"Rig=
ht arrow" width=3D"32" height=3D"30"> buttons, as shown below (all other bo=
xes can be ignored):
	<div class=3D"spss-image" style=3D"max-width:535px;max-height:470px;"><img=
