tics. Variables transferred on the right" width=3D"100%"><p>Published with =
written permission from SPSS Statistics, IBM Corporation.</p>
			</div>
	<p class=3D"note"><span class=3D"note-title">Note:</span> For a standard m=
ultiple regression you should ignore the <img class=3D"spss-image-in-text" =
src=3D"https://statistics.laerd.com/spss-tutorials/img/mr/previous-button-f=
aded.png" alt=3D"Faded previous" width=3D"60" height=3D"24" border=3D"0"> a=
nd <img class=3D"spss-image-in-text" src=3D"https://statistics.laerd.com/sp=
ss-tutorials/img/mr/next-button.png" data-src=3D"img/mr/next-button.png" al=
t=3D"Next" width=3D"60" height=3D"24"> buttons as they are for sequential (=
